data.text:
[Verse 1]
Your cheeks are red
From the cold and from me
Your breath draws clouds
Little ghosts I can see

You stomp your boots
On the cracked front step
Bring the winter in
On your scarf and your laugh

[Chorus]
I’m in love with the snow in your hair
Melted drops on your collar
You lean in
And the world disappears
Every shiver gets smaller
If this season lasts forever
I don’t care
If I’m holding you
With snow in your hair

[Verse 2]
Mugs in our hands
Hands over the steam
You trace a heart
In the fog on the screen

The kettle sings
But you’re all that I hear
You say “it’s freezing”
So I pull you near (come here)

[Chorus]
I’m in love with the snow in your hair
Melted drops on your collar
You lean in
And the world disappears
Every shiver gets smaller
If this season lasts forever
I don’t care
If I’m holding you
With snow in your hair

[Bridge]
Outside
The tire tracks turn to lines
Inside
Your fingers loop through mine
Let the wind keep shaking every tree
Long as it keeps you here with me

[Chorus]
I’m in love with the snow in your hair
Melted drops on your collar
You lean in
And the world disappears
Every shiver gets smaller
If the springtime comes tomorrow
I’ll still swear
I first fell for you
With snow in your hair
data.title: Snow In Your Hair

data.text:
[Verse 1]
Cold air on the window
Your breath makes a little cloud
Coffee on the nightstand
Wool socks dragged across the ground

[Pre-Chorus]
You laugh
My hands are shaking
As I zip your coat up tight
The whole world feels like it’s fading
Till it’s only us in white

[Chorus]
You got snow in your hair
Red on your cheeks
You say
“It’s freezing”
I say
“Stay close to me”
If this is forever
Let it start right here
Hands in your pockets
And snow in your hair

[Verse 2]
Sidewalks turned to silver
Our footprints in crooked lines
Your glove slips
I catch it
Like I’ve done a thousand times

[Pre-Chorus]
Street signs blur behind you
While you talk about next year
I’m memorizing every
Falling flake that lands near

[Chorus]
You got snow in your hair
Red on your cheeks
You say
“It’s freezing”
I say
“Stay close to me”
If this is forever
Let it start right here
Hands in your pockets
And snow in your hair

[Bridge]
Maybe in July
We’ll forget this kind of cold
But I’ll still taste the winter
On every story that we told
Right here on this corner
Where you pulled me into you
And promised me a season
That never quite feels through

[Chorus]
You got snow in your hair
Red on your cheeks
You say
“It’s freezing”
I say
“Stay close to me”
If this is forever
Let it start right here
Hands in your pockets
And snow in your hair

data.text:
[Verse]
Streetlights glitter
Snowflakes tumble slow
Another winter
Where did my warm feelings go

[Prechorus]
My hands are cold
My story untold

[Chorus]
You're my fire
You're my flame
You're my burning desire
Whispering your name

[Verse 2]
Jack Frost nipping
At my frozen nose
My heart keeps slipping
Through winter's icy throes

[Bridge]
The world outside is white and still
But inside me a warmth does thrill
A spark a flicker a growing light
You chase away the endless night

[Chorus]
You're my fire
You're my flame
You're my burning desire
Whispering your name
data.title: Frozen Heart Thaw

data.text:
[Verse]
Streetlights blur the falling snow
My heart it beats a steady flow
You walked right in my frosty day
And chased the winter blues away

[Prechorus]
Cold winds bite my rosy cheeks
Your warm hand is all I seek

[Chorus]
Oh winter love oh winter love
Sent from the stars up above
Winter love my winter love
Like a soft white dove

[Verse 2]
The coffee steams our breath it clouds
Lost in city crowds
Your smile it melts the ice inside
Nowhere left for me to hide

[Bridge]
They say that spring brings new romance
But our love is a winter dance
Every flake a tiny kiss
Pure and cold and utter bliss

[Chorus]
Oh winter love oh winter love
Sent from the stars up above
Winter love my winter love
Like a soft white dove

Look at you in that second-hand suit
Laughing like you did at twenty-two

data.title: To My Newlywed Friend

data.text:
[Verse 1]
We were kids in bad tuxedos
Laughing ‘til our faces hurt
Now you’re standing in a doorway
Straightening that brand new shirt
I watched you learn to parallel park
Burn toast
Chase every plan
Now you’re learning how a promise
Feels on your left hand

[Chorus]
Congratulations
My friend
Look at this life you stepped in
From late nights talking in your car
To sharing closets
Sharing hearts
May your mornings start with coffee
And end with fingers intertwined
Congratulations
My friend
You found a hand that matches mine (in time)

[Verse 2]
There were breakups in the kitchen
Tears on my old couch
Saying
“Maybe love’s not for me”
Well
Who’s laughing now?
Saw your name beside another
On a little folded card
It hit me like a blessing
Love was playing the long part

[Chorus]
Congratulations
My friend
Look at this life you stepped in
From late nights talking in your car
To sharing closets
Sharing hearts
May your arguments stay gentle
And your makeups taste like wine
Congratulations
My friend
You found a hand that fits just right with yours and time

data.text:
[Verse 1]
We were kids sharing secrets
Laughing till the sun went down
Now I'm straightening this tie
Watching you turn life around
You were late to every party
Now you're early to this vow
Funny how these little stories
Led you right here
Led you now

[Chorus]
Congratulations
My friend
Look at all that you’ve found
Hand in hand at the altar
Both feet off the ground
Here’s to mornings and dishes
All the boring turned bright
Congratulations
My friend
You two got it so right (oh yeah)

[Verse 2]
I remember cheap pizza
On a Tuesday
Talking big
You said
“Who’s gonna love me
When I still dance like a kid?”
Now you’re spinning in a white dress
They’re grinning ear to ear
Every hope you once whispered
I can see it standing here

[Chorus]
Congratulations
My friend
Look at all that you’ve found
Hand in hand at the altar
Both feet off the ground
Here’s to arguments softened
And your “sorry”s said light
Congratulations
My friend
You two got it so right

[Bridge]
Save this song for the hard days
Play it loud when you’re not okay
Let it remind you of this room
And the way their eyes chose you (hey!)

[Chorus]
Congratulations
My friend
Look at all that you’ve found
Hand in hand in the kitchen
Spinning slow
No one around
Here’s to ordinary magic
Making every day bright
Congratulations
My friend
May this love hold you tight

data.prompt:
[Verse 1]
Woke up to gold on my window
Dust in the air doing slow turns
Coffee cup hot in my left hand
Your name on my screen and my heart burns

[Chorus]
Sunshine on repeat
Running through my chest like a heartbeat
Every little ray has your heartbeat
Lighting up the corners of my mind
Sunshine on repeat
Spilling on the floor where our feet meet
Turning every Monday to sweet heat
Leave the cloudy days behind

[Verse 2]
Laugh lines deep in our selfies
Sidewalk chalk on your blue jeans
Traffic hums soft in the background
You spin me around like a daydream (hey!)

[Chorus]
Sunshine on repeat
Running through my chest like a heartbeat
Every little ray has your heartbeat
Lighting up the corners of my mind
Sunshine on repeat
Spilling on the floor where our feet meet
Turning every Monday to sweet heat
Leave the cloudy days behind

[Bridge]
If the rain comes in
Let it
We got bright stored up inside
Pull the curtains back
Set it free
Watch the shadows run and hide (oh)

[Chorus]
Sunshine on repeat
Running through my chest like a heartbeat
Every little ray has your heartbeat
Lighting up the corners of my mind
Sunshine on repeat
Spilling on the floor where our feet meet
Turning every Monday to sweet heat
Leave the cloudy days behind
data.tags: pop, Bright pop with glossy acoustic guitar and snappy drums, light synth plucks filling the edges. Female vocals, crisp and playful. Verses stay tight and bouncy; chorus explodes with stacked harmonies and claps. Middle lift adds a brief dreamy pad swell before dropping back into a final, hook-heavy chorus.
data.title: Sunshine On Repeat
